                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The letters are fairly simply engraved in a somewhat crude and broad V-cut, with minimal serifs at the terminations of the strokes. The letter V is rounded into a continuous stroke at the base. In the upper lines the letters are generously spaced, but they become more compressed and taller and thinner from line 4 onwards. The words are separated by ornate interpuncts in the form of a small s; a hedera is preserved at the end of the text.</p>
